{"title_page": "Ravi Nitesh Srivastava", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Ravi Nitesh Srivastava\n| image = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1981|08|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Basti district]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], India\n| occupation = Social activist and Columnist\n| parents = \n| awards = \n}}\n\n'''Ravi Nitesh Srivastava''' (born 1981) is an Indian social worker and columnist at Daily Times- Pakistan and regular contributor with various others newspapers/portals.<ref>https://dailytimes.com.pk/writer/ravi-nitesh/</ref><ref>https://countercurrents.org/author/ravi-nitesh</ref><ref>https://www.dnaindia.com/authors/ravi-nitesh</ref><ref>https://nayadaur.tv/author/ravinitesh/</ref><ref>https://thecompanion.in/author/ravi/</ref> His main areas of Work is Peace and Human Rights, through ground activism and writing.\n\n== Early life ==\n\nRavi Nitesh Srivastava was born on 16 August 1981. He is Graduate (B.Tech) in Mechanical Engineering and Post Graduate (M.Tech.) in Gas Engineering. Also had PG Diploma in Human Rights.<ref>http://upes.academia.edu/RAVINITESH</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\nHe is core member of Save Sharmila Solidarity Campaign, a nationwide protest to highlight the cause of [[Irom Chanu Sharmila]].<ref>https://blogs.lse.ac.uk/southasia/2014/09/26/irom-sharmila-the-worlds-longest-hunger-strike-in-the-worlds-largest-democracy/</ref> He had been featured as 'Ambassador of Harmony' by Asian Age.<ref>http://archive.asianage.com/life-and-style/ambassador-harmony-574</ref> His co-authored an e-book with Devika Mittal, published by [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]].<ref>https://www.amazon.com/INDO-PAK-RELATION-MEMOIRS-EMOTIONS-ebook/dp/B00CDRUYI6</ref> He is one of the over 200 concerned citizens of Indian and Pakistani have called for peace, insisting on the need for a \u2018un-interrupted and un-interruptible\u2019 dialogue to resolve all issues while maintaining peace and civilised bilateral relations. <ref>https://www.thecitizen.in/index.php/en/NewsDetail/index/2/10621/Citizens-of-India-and-Pakistan-Call-for-Peace</ref> Oxford Human Rights Hub (The Faculty of Law), University of Oxford published a article on his work on Indo-Pak fishermen.<ref>http://ohrh.law.ox.ac.uk/the-plight-of-indo-pak-fishermen-and-the-need-to-appreciate-economic-rights/ravi-nitesh/</ref> His role of activists and media in AFSPA.<ref>https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=1954286</ref> He was attended a seminar in Faizabad, at discussion on \u2018Terrorism is the biggest threat to humanity\u2019 organized at the Press Club Faizabad by Manav Ekta Manch in 2016.<ref>http://muslimmirror.com/eng/seminar-in-faizabad-activists-flay-politics-of-polarization/</ref>\n\n== References ==\n", "text_old": "{{User sandbox}}\n<!-- EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Ravi Nitesh Srivastava\n| image = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1981|08|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Basti district]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], India\n| occupation = Social activist and Columnist\n| parents = \n| awards = \n}}\n\n'''Ravi Nitesh Srivastava''' (born 1981) is an Indian social worker and columnist at Daily Times- Pakistan and regular contributor with various others newspapers/portals.<ref>https://dailytimes.com.pk/writer/ravi-nitesh/</ref><ref>https://countercurrents.org/author/ravi-nitesh</ref><ref>https://www.dnaindia.com/authors/ravi-nitesh</ref><ref>https://nayadaur.tv/author/ravinitesh/</ref><ref>https://thecompanion.in/author/ravi/</ref> His main areas of Work is Peace and Human Rights, through ground activism and writing.\n\n== Early life ==\n\nRavi Nitesh Srivastava was born on 16 August 1981. He is Graduate (B.Tech) in Mechanical Engineering and Post Graduate (M.Tech.) in Gas Engineering. Also had PG Diploma in Human Rights.<ref>http://upes.academia.edu/RAVINITESH</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\nHe is core member of Save Sharmila Solidarity Campaign, a nationwide protest to highlight the cause of [[Irom Chanu Sharmila]].<ref>https://blogs.lse.ac.uk/southasia/2014/09/26/irom-sharmila-the-worlds-longest-hunger-strike-in-the-worlds-largest-democracy/</ref> He had been featured as 'Ambassador of Harmony' by Asian Age.<ref>http://archive.asianage.com/life-and-style/ambassador-harmony-574</ref> His co-authored an e-book with Devika Mittal, published by [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]].<ref>https://www.amazon.com/INDO-PAK-RELATION-MEMOIRS-EMOTIONS-ebook/dp/B00CDRUYI6</ref> He is one of the over 200 concerned citizens of Indian and Pakistani have called for peace, insisting on the need for a \u2018un-interrupted and un-interruptible\u2019 dialogue to resolve all issues while maintaining peace and civilised bilateral relations. <ref>https://www.thecitizen.in/index.php/en/NewsDetail/index/2/10621/Citizens-of-India-and-Pakistan-Call-for-Peace</ref> Oxford Human Rights Hub (The Faculty of Law), University of Oxford published a article on his work on Indo-Pak fishermen.<ref>http://ohrh.law.ox.ac.uk/the-plight-of-indo-pak-fishermen-and-the-need-to-appreciate-economic-rights/ravi-nitesh/</ref> His role of activists and media in AFSPA.<ref>https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=1954286</ref> He was attended a seminar in Faizabad, at discussion on \u2018Terrorism is the biggest threat to humanity\u2019 organized at the Press Club Faizabad by Manav Ekta Manch in 2016.<ref>http://muslimmirror.com/eng/seminar-in-faizabad-activists-flay-politics-of-polarization/</ref>\n\n== References ==\n", "name_user": "Ged UK", "label": "safe", "comment": "rm user sandbox template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ravi_Nitesh_Srivastava"}
